systemd-cron (2.1.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  Starting with version 2.1.0, systemd-cron sends e-mail with job output
  if the job succeeds and output anything, matching classic cron behaviour.

  To return to pre-2.1.0 behaviour ‒ only sending mail on job failure ‒
  set CRON_MAIL_SUCCESS=never in /etc/crontab.
  To configure full classic-cron compat ‒ sending just the job output ‒
  set CRON_MAIL_FORMAT=nometadata in /etc/crontab.

  See crontab(5) and systemd.cron(7) for more on tuning the new mail system.

